{
  "texts": [
    "The time-delay measurement for image SX from subsequent monitoring is 376.0 +5.6 -5.5 days relative to image S1 (Kelly et al. 2023b).",
    "This time-delay measurement with a relative uncertainty of 1.5% provides the first opportunity for a precise H 0 measurement from lensed SNe, which we describe more in Sect. 2.3.",
    "The first spatially resolved multiply-imaged Type Ia supernova, iPTF16geu, was detected by the intermediate Palomar Transient Factory (Goobar et al. 2017).",
    "As shown in Fig. 2, the ground-based imager at iPTF could not spatially resolve the very compact system with Einstein radius θ E = 0.3.",
    "However, because of the \"standard candle\" nature of SNe Ia, it became clear that strong lensing was the most likely explanation, since the SN was more than 30 standard deviations brighter than the expectations for a SN Ia at its measured redshift, z = 0.409."
  ]
}